    "body": "### Language server\n\nbicep\n\n### Requested feature\n\nBicep parameter files (.bicepparam) are now preferred over json parameter files for bicep deploymentsâ€”more info [here](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-resource-manager/bicep/parameter-files?tabs=Bicep).\r\n\r\nI'm pretty sure the LSP already supports this filetype, but I've not been able to get this working in my config:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal bicep_bin = vim.fn.stdpath(\"data\") .. \"/mason/packages/bicep-lsp/extension/BicepLanguageServer/Bicep.LangServer.dll\"\r\nlspconfig.bicep.setup{\r\n  on_attach = on_attach,\r\n  capabilities = capabilities,\r\n  filetypes = { \"bicep\", \"bicepparam\" },\r\n  cmd = { \"dotnet\", bicep_bin },\r\n}\r\n```\r\nPlease let me know if this is something I've done incorrectly or if it is possible to extend support to the file extension. TIA\n\n### Other clients which have this feature\n\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": "2023-08-14T00:14:42Z",
