            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I've managed to get this working. It turns out bicepparam files _are_ supported, they're just not captured under the bicep file type.\r\nTo fix this, I've added the following autocmd to my config:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal autocmd = vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd\r\nlocal augroup = vim.api.nvim_create_augroup\r\n\r\nlocal general = augroup(\"General Settings\", { clear = true })\r\n\r\nautocmd(\"BufEnter\", {\r\n  pattern = \"*.bicepparam\",\r\n  callback = function()\r\n    vim.bo.filetype = \"bicep\"\r\n  end,\r\n  group = general,\r\n  desc = \"Set bicepparam filetype to bicep\",\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd so far so good. All syntax highlighting looks correct.",
